Creating an always solvable minesweeper

Required CUDA (CUDA enabled Nvidia GPU)

Started as project for Parallel class
Project page:
http://www.andrew.cmu.edu/user/cverkler/418_final/
Final Report Page:
http://www.andrew.cmu.edu/user/cverkler/418_final/finalreport.html

See links for description of goals

No GUI currently, just text

To use:
Auguents: -h height : height of the grid
-w width : width of the grid
-b number_of_bombs : number of bombs in the grid
-t : flag; display run times for various parts of the algorithm
-k : flag; display known grid
-d : flag; display debug grids

To play enter in grid coordinate : x y
To flag a grid enter : x y f